The paper discusses Bayesian inference for deep neural networks in the context of large scale image classification tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of deep neural networks using Bayesian inference, which is a core topic in machine learning. cs.CV is also a likely category as the paper specifically tests the proposed algorithm on image classification benchmarks. cs.AI and cs.NE are also possible categories as they are related to machine learning and neural networks. cs.CL is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on natural language processing or computational linguistics.
